Test Vector 1 — Single‑Variable Pass‑Through (Claim 1)

· Input (Phase 2 output format):

```json
{
  "status": "OK",
  "reduced_constraints": [
    {
      "identity_string": "[>",["var","x"],["int",5]]",
      "var": "x",
      "op": ">",
      "value": 5
    }
  ]
}
```

· Expected Phase 3 result:
  · status must be "OK".
  · The canonical_constraints list must contain exactly one entry.
  · That entry must have:
    · identity_string equal to the input identity string.
    · classification equal to "LINEAR_SINGLE_VAR".
    · canonical_form equal to "x >= 6" (integer tightening of x > 5).

